text: Kennet Kjensli (born 10 March 1969) is a Norwegian athlete who competed in sprinting events. He represented his country at two World Indoor Championships, in 1993 and 1995, reaching the semifinals on the first occasion. ==International competitions== {| |- !colspan="6"|Representing |- |1989 |European Indoor Championships |The Hague, Netherlands |19th (h) |60 m |6.84 |- |rowspan=2|1990 |European Indoor Championships |Glasgow, United Kingdom |18th (h) |60 m |6.83 |- |European Championships |Split, Yugoslavia | – |4 × 100 m relay |DNF |- |1992 |European Indoor Championships |Genoa, Italy |8th (sf) |60 m |6.71 |- |1993 |World Indoor Championships |Toronto, Canada |11th (sf) |60 m |6.72 |- |rowspan=2|1994 |European Indoor Championships |Paris, France |11th (sf) |60 m |6.75 |- |European Championships |Helsinki, Finland |16th (sf) |100 m |10.62 |- |1995 |World Indoor Championships |Barcelona, Spain |29th (h) |60 m |6.82 |} ==Personal bests== Outdoor *100 metres – 10.26 (+0.5 m/s, Lappeenranta 1994) Indoor *60 metres – 6.69 (Genoa 1992) ==References== *All-Athletics profile Category:1969 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian male sprinters
